      • decompress

        public InBuilder decompress()
        This method will tell the builder to decompress the bytes. The returned reader or stream will contain an appropriate decompressor. If the defined source specifies a name with a file ending, the builder will try to use the appropriate decompressor for the file extension. If there is no extension or it is unknown this simply adds a DeflaterOutputStream to the chain. If you want to add file extensions to the automatic selection see CompressorRegistry.registerWrapper(java.lang.String, com.github.power.io.helper.InputStreamWrapper, com.github.power.io.helper.OutputStreamWrapper).
        Returns:
        this builder

      • streamLines

        public java.util.stream.Stream<java.lang.String> streamLines()
                                                      throws java.io.IOException
        This method reads the complete input in a Stream of Strings. Each element of the stream represents one line of the source document. The stream is lazily populated. Be aware that the created reader is only closed if the created stream is fully explored. This means this operation should not be used with Stream.findAny() or similar terminal operations or the underlying stream will not be closed. Use readAll().stream() if you require these methods. This method uses the default Charset.
        Returns:
        a String containing the whole content of the file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if any element of the chain throws an IOException
